# Verify the notify-wait Drift Is Resolved

## Step

`system-bus-host-learner-flow/action` failed 2026-07-19T17:03Z on `joelclaw notify wait` "Invalid subcommand". Determine whether source or binary drift and whether it is fixed.

## Result (2026-07-20)

Stale installed binary, not source drift. The source (`learner-flow-actions.ts:246-268`) and CLI registration (`notify.ts:195-259`) were already correct; the installed `~/.bun/bin/joelclaw` predated the command. It was rebuilt 2026-07-19 22:56 (per the retry-storm incident receipt in `.brain/projects/messaging-stabilization/`) and now lists `notify wait` — verified live this session. Residual proof: the next `learner-flow/action` run completing without the error. No code change needed.
